Package msp.simulator.environment.orbit

Class Orbit.OrbitalParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • msp.simulator.environment.orbit.Orbit.OrbitalParameters
  • Enclosing class:
    Orbit

    public static class Orbit.OrbitalParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    This embedded class is used to build the orbit of the simulation. It consists basically in the main orbital parameters and the date of definition. This class also enables to change the default orbit with some user defined specific orbit.
    Author:
    Florian CHAUBEYRE

        public OrbitalParameters​(double altitude,
                         double ex,
                         double ey,
                         double i,
                         double raan,
                         double trueLatitude,
                         java.lang.String dateUtc)
        Explicit constructor for specific user-defined orbit at the defined date.
        Parameters:
        altitude - in meter
        ex - Eccentricity on X
        ey - Eccentricity on Y
        i - Inclinaison
        raan - Right ascension of the ascending node
        trueLatitude - true latitude
        dateUtc - String format of the date, e.g. "2018-12-21T22:23:00.000"
